guantanamo page 1 journalist carol rosenberg wednesday nov 16 4 30 6 00 pm bldg 260 room 113 stanford for nine years carol rosenberg has covered the proceedings in the us prison camps in guantanamo bay for the miami herald in 2011 her efforts were recog nized and she was awarded the robert f kennedy journalism award for her out standing reporting on human rights and social justice at the time of her award the rfk center for justice and human rights reported that rosenberg had logged more time at guantanamo than any other reporter taking on the task of ensuring that this important story is not forgotten in this talk rosenberg will focus on the challenges of operating as a journalist in guantanamo bay and the ethical issues that working there entails this event is free and open to the public ethicsinsociety stanford edu sponsors include the mccoy family center for ethics in society the knight fellowships program stanford says no to war america's experiment in extraterritorial detention
